				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">wow... that's about all i can say.  This is one of the most ignorant posts ever...
<br />

<br />
The reason you had a problem beating a DC pet is becuase a DC pet is like your pet fighting a mob who's been buffed by the person who charmed the DC pet.  So if you're fighting a Young Wrulan that's been DC'd and buffed it's going to be stronger than a standard Young Wrulan.  Before you start whining about how bad the "DC pet" beat your pet, try having just your pet solo a Young Wrulan (i'm assuming this is what was DC'd) or whatever was charmed.  I'm sure you'll find that your pet does not do very well against the mob when it's not buffed up. 
<br />

<br />
You also should learn about the downfalls of DC pets, most notably they eat xp.  So if you have a DC pet doing a significant portion of your dmg you're not going to get all of the xp.  I vaguely remember reading that this penalty could be up to 75% if the DC pet did 100% of the dmg.  I think it was a 50% penalty if the pet did over 50% of the dmg.  Absor had posted information about this when DC was being tuned (before PoP).  Now the DC pet eating xp is not limited to hunting solo.  It will eat some xp even in the person who controls the DC pet is in a group.  While I've had groups where DC pets have been a great benefit (inner in PoV) i've also had times where the DC pet seems to do nothing but absorb some of our xp, (wall camps PoV).  
<br />

<br />
The other most obvious downfall of DC pets is the lack of mobs that are DC charmable.  While there are mobs under lvl 45 in some xp zones they are hardly what i would consider common.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Also I would stay away from doing the "his pet is bigger than mine" comparison becuase there's a lot more to the magician class than the pet.  Yes the pet is a key factor in our class, and a good chunk of dmg output, but it's not the only thing that makes mages great.  Heck even with a DC'd pet I severly doubt that a druid's dmg output would be near a mages (or atleast mine).  
<br />

<br />

<br />
Falkahnhan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
