				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First, calm down a little.
<br />

<br />
Second, think about what you're saying.  Are you saying you find druids' charm overpowering?  Enchanters have even less restrictions on their charms than druids.
<br />

<br />
Wrulons quad for 159 max or so, with kick, and bash (I think).  Compared to 70-80s for normal pets.
<br />

<br />
The down side is, as mentioned, the exp taken.  Also, it's riskier than a normal pet, because if that charm breaks, druid is probably going to die if he isn't far enough away to get a root/snare down.  The enchanter is pretty much screwed.  However, the benefits are much higher with charm.  I have personally watched an enchanter solo Lodizal, with ease.
<br />

<br />
Similar to a melee discipline.  Most give an advantage, but have a disadvantage as well.  However, the gain is bigger than the downfall, thus it gets used.
<br />

<br />
Now, as for nerfing charm, I don't really see a feasible way.  You can make it to where it's so risky it wouldn't get used, but that is a little overboard.  Can't lower the capabilities of the mob either, because that's a player vs. environment issue.  Higher mana cost would be an idea, as it's trading the damage from DoTs/nukes into mana for the charm.
<br />

<br />
However, that's a druid issue.  Afraid you're a mage, and I'm just a pyromaniacal ranger. <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" />   Best to not go calling nerfs to other classes, unless you have played the class without anything higher than minor twinking/PL'ing.<br />_________________<br />Darlatan Firemist
<br />
60 ranger
<br />
League of Honour
<br />
Firiona Vie</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
