			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I never seen anyone been killed by a charmed DC pet, this aint a problem at all. 
<br />

<br />
More or less all PoP zones have a "DC pet", most of these are animal classes so druids can use them.  This include Elementals (some of them hit for 300+ too)
<br />
Most of these mobs have no reason to be in the zone, except for one reason, to be a DC pet (about 10-15level lower than other mobs, hit for 149 more or less always).
<br />

<br />
A standard Enchanter DC pet have around 6k hp, hit for 149, and will quad with weapons.  They more or less always keep up around 150dps, druid version do not always quad and they wont take weapons so they suffer a little in dmg.
<br />

<br />
There are three drawback with DCpets that really matters.
<br />
There is a 72min recycle of the skill.
<br />
You can't get them everywhere (they often placed at ZL).
<br />
They are kos to everything, combined with horrible pathing there are places you simply can't use them.
<br />

<br />

<br />
DC is a slap in the face against mages.
<br />
I don't want to see DC nerfed, but I want to see a few things fixed.
<br />
Give us DC charm summoned (and add a few summoned DC pets to some more zones), the old reason that we aint a charm class is not true anymore since we do get charm.
<br />
Remake our FB skill to acctually match the dps of a normal 149hiting DC pet (basicly make FB a perm buff on the pet it is casted on). 
<br />

<br />
Simple nice fixes, and NOONE should call them overpowered. (if you do you basicly say DC is overpowered and considering they added DC pets SOE aint considering DC overpowered)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
