			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In addition to stealing exp, SoE has been trying to limit the ability of DC pets from dual wielding.  I'm not sure if they've fixed it entirely, but I remember an enchanter DCing a double hitting pet who dind't normally duel wield would when given weapons.  After a few patches that changed.
<br />

<br />
DC pets and regular charmed pets have problems as well as enormous benefits.  Is it balanced?  /shrug.  All I know is I haven't seen any evidence that DC is why enchanters and druids are being accepted into raiding guilds (although an enchanters ability to use REAL charm is useful on a few encounters), and being chosen in groups over a mage.
<br />

<br />
I have a druid.  I almost made him my main.  But I dumped him at 30.  I didn't quite like his method of soloing at the time.  I liked my mage more in groups.  And I wasn't gonna slog it out to 59 and 27AA to get Dire Charm.  
<br />

<br />
The things I like about my pet have nothing to do with their precise DPS:
<br />
- They are summonable in just about any zone.
<br />
- They can be suspended when I need to invis to another part of the zone or need to pet canni for mana.
<br />
- They are indifferent to other mobs (DC pets are not).
<br />
- They respond to Summon Companion
<br />
- If they die to enrage I can summon another one immediately.
<br />

<br />
With charm or DC enchanters and druids can outsolo us pretty handily.  But in the soloing department so can necros and bards.  Its possible beastlords can as well.  Rangers with enough AA are FAR above the DPS of ANY of these classes.  I still don't care.
<br />
 
<br />
I still get enjoyment from my class and have little touble getting groups inside and outside of my guild.  My guild needs fewer mages than it needs druids, clerics, warriors, wizards, rogues, rangers, enchanters.  But I'm in the same boat as beastlords, sk, monks, shaman and necros.  A few of each class is enough and is rarely heavily recruited.
<br />

<br />
What does in <span style="font-style: italic">mean</span>?  Who knows.  In the right circumstances several classes outdamage and outsolo us.  But I do just about the same amount of damage in almost ANY zone.  There are a few raids my pet is not welcome or gets killed by AEs, and varying resists limit the damage of my nukes.  But in general I do the same thing in pretty much any zone I fight in.  Solo, group or raid: DS, mod rod, pet, nuke, malo-, and summon stuff.  My situational spells are rarely used: summon-only mez and charm and CoH.
<br />

<br />
In short I don't think DC is a balance issue for mages.  I wouldn't mind getting DC, but I don't feel I need it to be a good mage.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=341305">Izarek</a>
<br />
Pak'Cafan
<br />
Tarew Marr</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
