				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Druid DC is situational, same with Enchanter DC.  It is all a matter of how you look at it.  If it really bothers you this much, do the following:
<br />

<br />
-Ding lvl 65, get Call of the Archmage, Elemental Silence and head to BoT
<br />
-Charm an elemental, BOV and watch it quad in the 450s (I've parsed lightning elemental DPS ~ 400-450 DPS).
<br />
-Smile at the druid whose only pet is a lvl 35 bear.
<br />
-Run for your life when charm breaks.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Each class it's own strengths and weaknesses.  There are some cool abilities / spells that druids get that would be nice, but as it stands I prefer how the mage class is.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=653282" target=_blank>Sage Casala, Arch Convoker of Saryrn</a>
